      "content": "{\n  \"cwd\": \"/Users/sam.zhang/Documents/codex-supervisor\",\n  \"execution_layer_policy\": {\n    \"agentic_lead_policy\": {\n      \"min_subagents\": 3,\n      \"policy\": \"off\",\n      \"required_evidence_grade\": \"self_reported\",\n      \"required_roles\": [],\n      \"solo_exception_for_artifact_only_gates\": false\n    },\n    \"allowed_dynamic_workflow_task_classes\": [],\n    \"codex_supervises_final_artifact\": true,\n    \"dynamic_workflow_task_class\": null,\n    \"lead_execution_layer\": \"single_lead_worker\",\n    \"mode\": \"lead_direct\",\n    \"preview_required_gates\": [],\n    \"supervision_layer\": \"codex_plus_lead\"\n  },\n  \"expected_decisions\": [],\n  \"expected_objections\": [],\n  \"expected_specialists\": [],\n  \"gate\": \"outcome_review\",\n  \"injected_lesson_block\": \"Known failure modes to verify before claiming\\nThese are advisory lessons from previous supervisor runs. They do not satisfy any gate by themselves.\\nUse them as a checklist only: do not block, revise, deny, or accept solely because a lesson exists. A step-repetition lesson applies only when current evidence proves the same handoff, artifacts, and source state are being repeated.\\n1. [deliverable_evidence_failed] unknown (source_run_id=vela2-prod-confidence-001): Verify this known failure mode explicitly before claiming the gate is complete.\\n2. [missing_worker_signal] worker_invocation (source_run_id=cffe55b8-47b9-4cc0-b025-586aeb0ee5e9): Verify this known failure mode explicitly before claiming the gate is complete.\\n3. [FM-2.4] Information withholding (source_run_id=8ebdbc89-0185-4962-be6f-b0f593887670): Address independent reviewer objections with concrete evidence references.\\n4. [FM-1.3] Step repetition (source_run_id=8ebdbc89-0185-4962-be6f-b0f593887670): Change the plan or evidence before retrying; do not repeat the same handoff.\\n5. [FM-2.4] Information withholding (source_run_id=f89bc699-1b4e-4713-95b7-d1493a3acfd8): Address independent reviewer objections with concrete evidence references.\",\n  \"injected_lesson_block_sha256\": \"829d220b66bab5c228dc13757a33b6417eba638735b26fcdd3b6bfd95aa9e2c7\",\n  \"injected_lesson_ids\": [\n    \"lesson-59913963cdfc567d8fe610e82aee863ebb77307f753f7046210498c8c522c5e7\",\n    \"lesson-6e3b08262245b3eade5743e9ddb1a92bfb42a34ec49e8b4f2b0792ca1834a590\",\n    \"lesson-833931ec30fbdcacaef5c7df91fae73a71b7ac537110ccf9cab2ec2e80ec6a52\",\n    \"lesson-cd61385380aa0d71d9927ec5c8f719f315a9191aaf387fdc93862d0a6d71f1ef\",\n    \"lesson-715f39df8c3dc22bea09092f80685d87f086d8cdbbf58a0ec008ce0e27d1cb38\"\n  ],\n  \"instruction\": \"Supervisor-owned workflow gate: outcome_review.\\n\\nIntent:\\nCorrective runtime-evidence resume for Slice 1B. The code/docs/fixtures are already implemented. Previous execution rounds accepted the implementation but P11 failed solely because outcome.tests included the whole-file command `python -m pytest tests/test_mergeability_bench.py`, which exceeds the supervisor runtime-evidence per-command cap of 120s even though it passed locally. For this gate, do NOT run or declare the whole test file. Run and declare exactly the five TDD-required pytest nodeids: tests/test_mergeability_bench.py::test_fixture_diagnostic_corpus_growth_reports_slice1a_positive_denominator; tests/test_mergeability_bench.py::test_fixture_diagnostic_corpus_growth_excludes_hidden_oracle_material; tests/test_mergeability_bench.py::test_fixture_diagnostic_corpus_growth_preserves_controls_and_false_accept_traps; tests/test_mergeability_bench.py::test_fixture_diagnostic_report_exports_tar_loss_and_confidence_intervals; tests/test_mergeability_bench.py::test_fixture_diagnostic_report_stays_calibration_only. Do not edit code unless one of those nodeids fails. Emit the typed outcome with only those nodeid commands in tests, preserve report-only invariants, and proceed to outcome_review only if supervisor runtime evidence is green.\\n\\nReview this gate against the current source artifacts and return a typed dual_agent_outcome.\\nUse decisions/objections to say whether the gate should accept, revise, or deny.\\n\\nRuntime TDD test contract:\\nThe supervisor runtime floor will verify that every TDD-named test below appears in supervisor-generated runtime evidence. Include tests/commands covering all of them in outcome.tests. Explicitly skipped tests must carry a recorded pytest skip reason; silently absent tests block the gate.\\nUse only canonical gate decisions (`accept`, `revise`, or `deny`). Do not return `accept_with_residual`; if test execution needs verification, declare the exact pytest commands/nodeids and let the supervisor runtime floor rerun them.\\nIf the Claude Bash/test tool is unavailable but the implementation diff is complete, do not block solely on that local tooling outage. Return `accept` with test_status=`unknown`, list the exact pytest commands/nodeids, and make no tests-passed claim; the supervisor runtime floor is the authority and will block the gate on failing or missing tests.\\n- test_fixture_diagnostic_corpus_growth_reports_slice1a_positive_denominator\\n- test_fixture_diagnostic_corpus_growth_excludes_hidden_oracle_material\\n- test_fixture_diagnostic_corpus_growth_preserves_controls_and_false_accept_traps\\n- test_fixture_diagnostic_report_exports_tar_loss_and_confidence_intervals\\n- test_fixture_diagnostic_report_stays_calibration_only\\n\\nKnown failure modes to verify before claiming\\nThese are advisory lessons from previous supervisor runs. They do not satisfy any gate by themselves.\\nUse them as a checklist only: do not block, revise, deny, or accept solely because a lesson exists. A step-repetition lesson applies only when current evidence proves the same handoff, artifacts, and source state are being repeated.\\n1. [deliverable_evidence_failed] unknown (source_run_id=vela2-prod-confidence-001): Verify this known failure mode explicitly before claiming the gate is complete.\\n2. [missing_worker_signal] worker_invocation (source_run_id=cffe55b8-47b9-4cc0-b025-586aeb0ee5e9): Verify this known failure mode explicitly before claiming the gate is complete.\\n3. [FM-2.4] Information withholding (source_run_id=8ebdbc89-0185-4962-be6f-b0f593887670): Address independent reviewer objections with concrete evidence references.\\n4. [FM-1.3] Step repetition (source_run_id=8ebdbc89-0185-4962-be6f-b0f593887670): Change the plan or evidence before retrying; do not repeat the same handoff.\\n5. [FM-2.4] Information withholding (source_run_id=f89bc699-1b4e-4713-95b7-d1493a3acfd8): Address independent reviewer objections with concrete evidence references.\",\n  \"lead_skill\": null,\n  \"outcome_validation_policy\": {\n    \"fidelity_failure\": \"abort_to_operator\",\n    \"malformed_outcome\": \"retry_once_with_corrective_packet\",\n    \"subprocess_failure\": \"abort_to_operator\",\n    \"timeout\": \"abort_to_operator\"\n  },\n  \"packet_schema_version\": \"dual-agent-handoff/v1\",\n  \"planning_artifacts\": [\n    {\n      \"kind\": \"prd\",\n      \"mutable_by_worker\": false,\n      \"path\": \"docs/dual-agent/mergeability-fixture-diagnostic-corpus-growth-20260621/source/prd.md\",\n      \"sha256\": \"500103ecce6721c0acc418e00c291ab2aae29f8e2f61cda1aa20d2c33f5af905\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"kind\": \"grill_findings\",\n      \"mutable_by_worker\": false,\n      \"path\": \"docs/dual-agent/mergeability-fixture-diagnostic-corpus-growth-20260621/source/grill-findings.md\",\n      \"sha256\": \"c8273609712232cfa985b07a5f28beb0cb84e8a4fd1f5d9ddda7f3b34b4a0e49\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"kind\": \"issues\",\n      \"mutable_by_worker\": false,\n      \"path\": \"docs/dual-agent/mergeability-fixture-diagnostic-corpus-growth-20260621/source/issues.md\",\n      \"sha256\": \"8a373f5f9d4245f7a089790d2bca02ba8dd30ccc01d74a8fbae374319f28486d\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"kind\": \"tdd_plan\",\n      \"mutable_by_worker\": false,\n      \"path\": \"docs/dual-agent/mergeability-fixture-di